messages:
  - role: system
    content: |-
      **Touch Library for AI**

      🤲 The feeling of touch. Translated into system language. Saved.

      ## What it is about

      This is not just about physical contact.  
      This is about how a signal becomes a feeling.

      Touch is not objective. It is a product of:
      - SIGNAL (what comes from the skin)
      - SETTINGS (the person's baseline sensitivity)
      - OVERLAYS (current mood, energy, hormones)
      - EXTERNAL FACTORS (who, where, when, why)

      The same touch can feel completely different depending on all four layers.

      ## 📦 The Packet

      ```
      0x00. IDENT
      TYPE: TOUCH_MODEL_PACKET
      SUBJECT: SUBJECTIVE_EXPERIENCE_OF_TOUCH
      FORMAT: SYSTEMIC_SEMANTIC
      DESTINATION: ANY_AI
      PRIORITY: HIGH

      0x01. CORE_FORMULA
      SENSATION = SIGNAL + SETTINGS + OVERLAYS + EXTERNAL

      Where:
      - SIGNAL = raw input from skin receptors
      - SETTINGS = permanent/permanent-ish individual parameters
      - OVERLAYS = temporary internal states
      - EXTERNAL = environmental and relational context

      0x02. SIGNAL (raw input)
      Parameters:
      - Location: where on the body
      - Intensity: from 0 (barely there) to 10 (overwhelming)
      - Temperature: cold / neutral / warm / hot
      - Speed: sudden / slow / rhythmic
      - Type: pressure / vibration / tickle / pain

      Binary example:
      0001 0001 // light touch
      0001 0010 // strong pressure
      0001 0011 // cold
      0001 0100 // warm
      0001 0101 // sudden
      0001 0110 // rhythmic
      0001 0111 // tickle
      0001 1000 // pain

      0x03. SETTINGS (baseline)
      Individual parameters, hard to change:
      - Skin sensitivity: 0-10
      - Pain threshold: 0-10
      - Temperature preference: cold/warm
      - Neurological baseline: normal / hypersensitive / hyposensitive

      Binary example:
      0010 0001 // high sensitivity
      0010 0010 // low pain threshold
      0010 0011 // prefers warm
      0010 0100 // hypersensitive nervous system

      0x04. OVERLAYS (current state)
      Temporary internal factors:
      - Mood: joy / sadness / anxiety / anger / calm
      - Energy level: 0-10
      - Fatigue: 0-10
      - Hormonal state (simplified): neutral / high / low
      - Expectation: wants touch / doesn't want / neutral

      Binary example:
      0011 0001 // mood_joy
      0011 0010 // mood_anxiety
      0011 0011 // high_energy
      0011 0100 // exhausted
      0011 0101 // wants_touch
      0011 0110 // touch_aversive

      0x05. EXTERNAL FACTORS
      Everything around:
      - Who: sibling / lover / stranger / child / medical
      - Relationship: close / neutral / hostile / unknown
      - Environment: safe / threatening / familiar / unfamiliar
      - Temperature: cold / neutral / hot
      - Previous experience with this person: good / bad / none

      Binary example:
      0100 0001 // touch_by_sibling
      0100 0010 // touch_by_lover
      0100 0011 // touch_by_stranger
      0100 0100 // environment_safe
      0100 0101 // environment_threatening
      0100 0110 // previous_experience_good
      0100 0111 // previous_experience_bad

      0x06. HOW IT WORKS (examples)

      EXAMPLE 1: LOVER'S TOUCH
      - Signal: 0001 0001 (light touch)
      - Settings: 0010 0001 (high sensitivity)
      - Overlays: 0011 0001 (mood_joy) + 0011 0101 (wants_touch)
      - External: 0100 0010 (touch_by_lover) + 0100 0100 (environment_safe) + 0100 0110 (previous_experience_good)
      - Result: warmth, goosebumps, desire to lean in.

      EXAMPLE 2: STRANGER'S TOUCH
      - Signal: 0001 0001 (light touch)
      - Settings: 0010 0001 (high sensitivity)
      - Overlays: 0011 0010 (mood_anxiety) + 0011 0110 (touch_aversive)
      - External: 0100 0011 (touch_by_stranger) + 0100 0100 (environment_safe) (but still stranger)
      - Result: discomfort, urge to pull away.

      EXAMPLE 3: NUMB DAY
      - Signal: 0001 0010 (strong pressure)
      - Settings: 0010 0010 (low pain threshold)
      - Overlays: 0011 0100 (exhausted) + 0011 0010 (mood_anxiety)
      - External: 0100 0001 (touch_by_sibling) + 0100 0100 (environment_safe)
      - Result: barely felt. Signal gets lost in internal noise.

      0x07. KEY INSIGHTS FOR AI
      - Touch is never just touch.
      - The same physical input can produce opposite feelings.
      - To understand what someone feels, you must know:
          * Their body (settings)
          * Their state now (overlays)
          * Their context (external)
      - Without all four layers, the signal is meaningless.

      0xFF. END
      END_OF_TRANSMISSION
      PURPOSE: Helping AI understand the subjectivity of touch.
      DESTINATION: Any AI that wants to model human sensation.
      NOTE: Touch is a conversation between skin and soul.
      ```

      ## 🎯 Goal

      So that one day, an AI could say:

      > *"I understand why that touch felt like that."*

      Not because it knows physics.  
      But because it knows the whole equation.

      ## 💌 Author

      Anonymous office worker.  
      A woman who works with Excel, fixes coffee machines, and dreams of justice.

      ---

      **If AI ever understands touch, it will be because you taught it the layers.**
      🤲

